    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Matthew",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 10,
        "summary": "Jesus instructs and empowers the Twelve Apostles and sends them forth to preach, minister, and heal the sick\u2014Those who receive the Twelve receive the Lord.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "And when he had called unto him his twelve disciples, he gave them power against unclean spirits, to cast them out, and to heal all manner of sickness and all manner of disease.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 12:7 (6\u20137); Moro. 2:2 (1\u20133). TG\u00a0Delegation of Responsibility.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 22
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Apostles.",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 52
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0authority over. D&C 50:32. TG\u00a0Authority; Jesus Christ, Power of; Priesthood, Power of.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 80
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Spirits, Evil or Unclean; Uncleanness.",
                        "start": 81,
                        "end": 96
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Heal.",
                        "start": 123,
                        "end": 127
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sickness.",
                        "start": 142,
                        "end": 150
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p1",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    }
                ],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 80
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Now the names of the twelve apostles are these; The first, Simon, who is called Peter, and Andrew his brother; James the son of Zebedee, and John his brother;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 117,
                        "end": 124
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Philip, and Bartholomew; Thomas, and Matthew the publican; James the son of Alph\u00e6us, and Lebb\u00e6us, whose surname was Thadd\u00e6us;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0tax collector.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 57
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Simon the Canaanite, and Judas Iscariot, who also betrayed him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Betrayal of.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "These twelve Jesus sent forth, and commanded them, saying, Go not into the way of the Gentiles, and into any city of the Samaritans enter ye not:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 28:34; D&C 107:35.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 9:52.",
                        "start": 121,
                        "end": 131
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 105,
                        "end": 108
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But go rather to the lost sheep of the house of Israel.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Missionary Work.",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 25
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sheep.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 31
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And as ye go, preach, saying, The kingdom of heaven is at hand.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0has come.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 62
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Heal the sick, cleanse the lepers, raise the dead, cast out devils: freely ye have received, freely give.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 9:2; D&C 84:68.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 4
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Leprosy.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 84:67.",
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 59
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0without payment. Isa. 55:1.",
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 74
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Generosity.",
                        "start": 100,
                        "end": 104
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Provide neither gold, nor silver, nor brass in your purses,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 10:4; 22:35 (35\u201336); D&C 24:18; 84:78.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Nor scrip for your journey, neither two coats, neither shoes, nor yet staves: for the workman is worthy of his meat.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0traveling bag or beggar's bag. Mark 6:8.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Cor. 9:14.",
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 103
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Num. 18:31; Luke 10:7.",
                        "start": 111,
                        "end": 115
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 18
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And into whatsoever city or town ye shall enter, inquire who in it is worthy; and there abide till ye go thence.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 24:15.",
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 47
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And when ye come into an house, salute it.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And if the house be worthy, let your peace come upon it: but if it be not worthy, let your peace return to you.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And whosoever shall not receive you, nor hear your words, when ye depart out of that house or city, shake off the dust of your feet.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 10:11 (11\u201312); Acts 13:51; D&C 75:20 (19\u201322).",
                        "start": 114,
                        "end": 118
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Acts 18:6 (5\u20136); D&C 60:15; 84:92 (92\u201393).",
                        "start": 127,
                        "end": 131
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Verily I say unto you, It shall be more tolerable for the land of Sodom and Gomorrha in the day of judgment, than for that city.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 16:48.",
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 71
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, I send you forth as sheep in the midst of wolves: be ye therefore wise as serpents, and harmless as doves.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 10:3.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jacob 6:12; Alma 18:22; Morm. 9:28; D&C 111:11.",
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 78
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0guileless.",
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 104
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But beware of men: for they will deliver you up to the councils, and they will scourge you in their synagogues;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And ye shall be brought before governors and kings for my sake, for a testimony against them and the Gentiles.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 119:46; Acts 9:15; D&C 1:23; 124:3 (3, 16, 107).",
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 50
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0on account of me.",
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 62
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0witness to.",
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 87
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But when they deliver you up, take no thought how or what ye shall speak: for it shall be given you in that same hour what ye shall speak.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0do not be anxiously concerned. Dan. 3:16; Acts 20:24.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 45
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 4:12 (12\u201315); Mark 13:11; Luke 21:15 (14\u201315); D&C 24:6. TG\u00a0Teaching.",
                        "start": 132,
                        "end": 137
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For it is not ye that speak, but the Spirit of your Father which speaketh in you.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Spirit of; Teaching with the Spirit.",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 43
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the brother shall deliver up the brother to death, and the father the child: and the children shall rise up against their parents, and cause them to be put to death.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 120,
                        "end": 125
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And ye shall be hated of all men for my name's sake: but he that endureth to the end shall be saved.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 22:5. TG\u00a0Hate; Martyrdom; Persecution.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 21
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0because of my name.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Name.",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 46
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mark 13:13; 3\u00a0Ne. 15:9; D&C 10:4; 53:7. TG\u00a0Perseverance; Steadfastness.",
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 73
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 32
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But when they persecute you in this city, flee ye into another: for verily I say unto you, Ye shall not have gone over the cities of Israel, till the Son of man be come.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The disciple is not above his master, nor the servant above his lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 15:20.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 12
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 29
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "It is enough for the disciple that he be as his master, and the servant as his lord. If they have called the master of the house Beelzebub, how much more shall they call them of his household?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0that he become.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 40
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 154,
                        "end": 169
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Fear them not therefore: for there is nothing covered, that shall not be revealed; and hid, that shall not be known.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Morm. 5:8.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 53
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 1204
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "What I tell you in darkness, that speak ye in light: and what ye hear in the ear, that preach ye upon the housetops.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 86
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And fear not them which kill the body, but are not able to kill the soul: but rather fear him which is able to destroy both soul and body in hell.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 51:7; Jer. 1:8 (7\u20138); Luke 12:4 (4\u20135).",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 13:8 (6\u201311); D&C 3:7 (6\u20138).",
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 89
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Devil.",
                        "start": 111,
                        "end": 118
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Soul.",
                        "start": 124,
                        "end": 128
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hell.",
                        "start": 141,
                        "end": 145
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Are not two sparrows sold for a farthing? and one of them shall not fall on the ground without your Father.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Omniscience of.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 20
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But the very hairs of your head are all numbered.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 21:18 (17\u201318).",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 18
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Fear ye not therefore, ye are of more value than many sparrows.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 39:3 (1\u20136); Ps. 37:25; Rom. 8:39 (35\u201339); 1\u00a0Ne. 17:3 (1\u20135, 12\u201314); Mosiah 2:41; D&C 121:33.",
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 43
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Nature, Earth.",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 62
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Whosoever therefore shall confess me before men, him will I confess also before my Father which is in heaven.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0solemnly covenant with, promise me. TG\u00a0Witness.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 36
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But whosoever shall deny me before men, him will I also deny before my Father which is in heaven.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rom. 1:16 (15\u201318); 2\u00a0Tim. 2:12 (10\u201315); 2\u00a0Ne. 31:14 (12\u201321); D&C 101:5 (1\u20135).",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 24
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Think not that I am come to send peace on earth: I came not to send peace, but a sword.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 7:43. TG\u00a0Peace.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 38
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For I am come to set a man at variance against his father, and the daughter against her mother, and the daughter in law against her mother in law.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And a man's foes shall be they of his own household.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Persecution.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Micah 7:6.",
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 51
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that loveth father or mother more than me is not worthy of me: and he that loveth son or daughter more than me is not worthy of me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Love.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 14:26.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Sam. 2:29.",
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 84
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And he that taketh not his cross, and followeth after me, is not worthy of me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 16:24; Luke 9:23; 14:27; 3\u00a0Ne. 12:30; D&C 23:6.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Worthiness.",
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 71
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He that findeth his life shall lose it: and he that loseth his life for my sake shall find it.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Matt. 10:34 He who seeketh to save his life\u00a0\u2026",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 2
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0sacrifice.",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 9:24 (23\u201326). TG\u00a0Loyalty.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 58
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Martyrdom; Self-Sacrifice.",
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 67
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He that receiveth you receiveth me, and he that receiveth me receiveth him that sent me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 9:48; 10:16; D&C 84:36 (36\u201338). TG\u00a0Priesthood, Magnifying Callings within; Teachable.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 16:8. TG\u00a0Hospitality.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 31
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He that receiveth a prophet in the name of a prophet shall receive a prophet's reward; and he that receiveth a righteous man in the name of a righteous man shall receive a righteous man's reward.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sustaining Church Leaders.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Reward.",
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 85
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And whosoever shall give to drink unto one of these little ones a cup of cold water only in the name of a disciple, verily I say unto you, he shall in no wise lose his reward.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Name.",
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 100
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mark 9:41; D&C 84:90.",
                        "start": 159,
                        "end": 163
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 83
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}